docking scrim
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:fibrous material made from flax. [Used elsewhere but particularly widely used in New Zealand hill country farming for making temporary yards for docking and for funnelling animals into a race or loading bank.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
